  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Or if his sin wherein he hath sinned come to his knowledge,.... Or rather, \"and if his sin\", &c. (m) either by means of others informing him of it, or of himself calling to mind what he has done, and considering it to be a transgression of the law: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "he shall bring his offering, a kid of the goats, a male without blemish; his offering was to be a \"kid of the goats\", a fat and a large one; because, as Baal Hatturim observes, he ate fat things every day; and to distinguish it from the offering of one of the common people; and \"without blemish\"; as all sacrifices were, that they might be typical of the offering of Christ without spot. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(m) Sept. \"et postea\", V. L. & Noldius, p. 3. No. 23. ",
        "children": [
